name: palmitoyl[protein] hydrolase
comment: Specific for long-chain thioesters of fatty acids. Hydrolyses fatty acids from S-acylated cysteine residues in proteins, palmitoyl cysteine and palmitoyl-CoA.

references.title: Assay and isolation of palmitoyl-protein thioesterase from bovine brain using palmitoylated H-Ras as substrate.
cDNA and genomic cloning of human palmitoyl-protein thioesterase (PPT), the enzyme defective in infantile neuronal ceroid lipofuscinosis.
